title.narrative: Government and Civil Society capacity to provide adolescent HIV prevention, treatment and care information and servicesstrengthened.

description.narrative: In 2020, the proportion of districts implementing at least three high impact adolescent HIV prevention initiatives increased from 97 percent in 2019 to %100 in 2020. With UNICEF Eswatini support to partners, all adolescent HIV interventions adapted to the COVID-19 pandemic to ensure adolescents continue to access the full range of services. 6,203 adolescents were tested for HIV and received their results. 3,036 adolescents living with HIV were provided adherence counselling, food, masks and sanitizers. Support to two local NGOs reached 8,706 in and out-of- school adolescents with comprehensive HIV and violence information through peer education sessions in the communities. | Status:Met | As-of Date:11/01/2021
